===By Coursework or Coursework & Dissertation===

*PI005 - Foundation in Law (Normal Track) (Three Semesters)	  
*PI005 - Foundation in Law (Fast Track) (Two Semesters)
*PI007 - Foundation in Law (Ministry of Higher Education) (Two Semesters with allowance and law degree courses will be done either in UiTM or other [[public universities]])
*LW213 - Bachelor of Legal Studies (Hons.) 
*LW222 - Bachelor of Laws (Hons.) 
*LW601 - Postgraduate Diploma in Syariah Law & Practice 
*LW775 - Master of Laws (LL.M)(Commercial Law)	 
*LW774 - Master of Laws (LL.M)(Public Interest Law)	
*LW772 - Master of Laws (LL.M)(Corporate Law)	  
*LW773 - Master of Laws (LL.M)(Legal Aspects of Marine)	  
*LW771 - Master of Laws (LL.M)(Intellectual Property)	
*LW770 - Master of Laws (LL.M)

===By Research===

*LW 781 - Master of Laws (LL.M)	  
*LW 991 - PhD in Law

==Centres of Excellence==

These Centres oversee conferences, seminars, workshop and research work in their respective fields.

*Centre for International Law
*Centre for Cyber Law and Policy
*Centre for Criminal Justice Studies 

==Law Students' Societies and Clubs==

UiTM Malaysia Law School has many students<U+2019> societies and clubs to help the students to be more independent, resourceful and all-rounder individuals.

*Sekreteriat Mahasiswa Fakulti (''Faculty Students Secreteriate'')
*Mooting Club [http://mootclubuitm.blogspot.com]
*Law Debating Club
*Students' Community Law Club (SCLC)
*Environmental Law & Awareness Club (EnLAC)

